            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>A Rallying Refrain for Breckinridge and Lane</head>
                <origin>Journal of Commerce</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Poem/song for the "gallant Lane and Breckinridge."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>Lincoln's Supporters</head>
                <origin>Dayton (Ohio) Empire</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Gives brief quotes that illustrate the radical beliefs of a number of
                    Lincoln supporters.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>Facts Worthy to be Considered</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Stresses that the quarrel with the South is being carried out by the
                    abolitionists of New England--Pennsylvanians shouldn't get involved.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>The Celebration of the Death of Old John Brown in Massachusetts</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Discussion of the commemoration of Brown's hanging. A Lincoln and Hamlin
                    club made up entirely of free blacks marched in the parade.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>03</column>
                <head>Lord Brougham on the Election</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Analysis of the presidential election, in which Brougham states that the
                    great question of the election "depends entirely upon the principles expressed
                    by the candidates respecting slavery."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>03</column>
                <head>Douglas in Alliance with Southern Secessionists</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Although Douglas spoke against secession in a recent speech in
                    Pennsylvania, the Spirit points out that he is in alliance with a secessionist:
                    his Vice Presidential candidate Hershel Johnson.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>04</column>
                <head>The Republican Party</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The opinions of John C. Calhoun and Henry Clay on abolitionists.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>04</column>
                <head>Was the Vice-Presidential Nomination on the Douglas Ticket Tendered to William
                    L. Yancey?</head>
                <origin>Richmond Enquirer</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Claims that Yancey was offered the vice presidential position on the
                    Douglas ticket at the Democratic convention. He turned it down, saying that "oil
                    and water do not mix."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>06</column>
                <head>The Presidential Race by "Sam Billings"</head>
                <origin>Charleston Courier</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Satirical story about a "race" between the presidential candidates.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
